The paper discusses a programming model for stencil-based computations on distributed memory architectures, which falls under the category of parallel and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of language extensions and program transformations, which are topics related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of this programming model for high-performance computing (cs.AR) and mentions the use of a data-parallel programming model, which is related to performance optimization (cs.PF).
